summary:
ByteScout PDF SDK for .NET, ASP.NET and ActiveX/COM.

Artifex Software, Inc. (c) 2016-2023.

ByteScout PDF SDK provides the rich and easy-to-use API to create PDF documents with text, images, drawings or modify existing PDF documents.

Compatibility: .NET Framework 2.0 or later; .NET Core 2.0 or later.
Works with: .NET, ASP.NET, ActiveX, Visual Basic 6, Classic ASP, VSBScript and others.

ONLINE DOCUMENTATION: http://bytescout.com/help/BytescoutPDFSDK/index.html

BENEFITS: 
- Full set of methods and properties to create or modify PDF documents;
- PNG, JPEG, TIFF, JBIG2, CCITT Fax images and image compression modes supported;
- Font embedding (Type1, TrueType) including Unicode support;
- Security options (document permissions) and 40 bit, 128 bit and 256 AES encryption support;
- Support for changing security settings of existing PDF documents (you can also remove the protection);
- Ability to handle produced PDF document in memory without need for temporary files and provide on-the-fly generation directly into memory stream (requires additional Web License);
- Ability to split, merge, extract pages from PDF document and append to another document using pages manager class;
- Per developer licensing (no royalty, no per CPU);

TRIAL VERSION LIMITATIONS:
- Adds reminder text messages to output document.

